      • getIndex

        public abstract int getIndex()
        The ordinal index of the variable that is bound by this BinderBase. By convention, index ZERO is the vertex. Indices greater than ZERO are typically aspects of the state of the vertex.

                                 org.openrdf.model.Value u,
                                 IVariable<?>[] outVars,
                                 IBindingSet bs)
        Call bind(ValueFactory, IGASState, Value).
        Specified by:
        bind in interface IBinder<VS,ES,ST>
        Parameters:
        vf - The ValueFactory used to create the return Value.
        state - The IGASState.
        u - The vertex.
        outVars - The array of output variables.
        bs - The current binding set. Can be used to conditionally bind values based on the current solution.
        Returns:
        The Value for that ordinal variable or null if there is no binding for that ordinal variable.
